    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you on the presentation part, but \"professionalism\" is pretty subjective, isn't it? In many modern tech companies or diverse environments, being able to connect with people on a human level is a huge plus. If Candidate B can resolve the issue just as effectively, why is the colloquial style a disqualifier? Don't you think labeling it as a lack of \"competence\" might be an unfair assumption based just on their dialect?",
